                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d43">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/8207: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-02-08T13:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 8, 1927—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 8—6:44 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>121. My 119, February 7, 5 p.m. Following from American consul general at Hankow:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“February 7, 11 a.m. My February 6, 2 p.m. General Chu, Chief of Staff,
                            informs me this morning that he has referred memorandum to Minister for
                            Foreign Affairs, which procedure was no doubt promptly arranged by Ch’en
                            after I saw him yesterday.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
